Q5: Configure a Jenkins pipeline to automate the building and deployment of a Dockerized application from GitHub

Step 1: Start Jenkins using Docker (Command Prompt)

Open Command Prompt and run:

docker volume create jenkins-data

docker run -d ^
--name jenkins ^
-p 8080:8080 ^
-p 50000:50000 ^
-v jenkins-data:/var/jenkins_home ^
-v /var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock ^
jenkins/jenkins:lts

Get Jenkins admin password:

docker exec jenkins cat /var/jenkins_home/secrets/initialAdminPassword

Open browser and go to:

http://localhost:8080

Paste the password and install suggested plugins

Step 2: Install Docker inside Jenkins (Command Prompt)

docker exec -u root jenkins bash -c "apt-get update && apt-get install -y docker.io"

Step 3: Prepare GitHub Repository

Open your GitHub repository

Create a new file named:

Jenkinsfile

Paste the following code:

pipeline {
agent any

```
environment {
    IMAGE_NAME = "myapp"
    DOCKER_HUB_USER = "jeevanjeraldm"
}

stages {

    stage('Clone') {
        steps {
            git branch: 'main',
            url: 'https://github.com/JeevanJeraldm/Devops-Lab.git'
        }
    }

    stage('Build Image') {
        steps {
            sh 'docker build -t $DOCKER_HUB_USER/$IMAGE_NAME:latest .'
        }
    }

    stage('Push to Hub') {
        steps {
            withCredentials([usernamePassword(
                credentialsId: 'dockerhub-creds',
                usernameVariable: 'DOCKER_USER',
                passwordVariable: 'DOCKER_PASS'
            )]) {
                sh '''
                echo $DOCKER_PASS | docker login -u $DOCKER_USER --password-stdin
                docker push $DOCKER_HUB_USER/$IMAGE_NAME:latest
                '''
            }
        }
    }

    stage('Deploy') {
        steps {
            sh 'docker run -d -p 5000:5000 $DOCKER_HUB_USER/$IMAGE_NAME:latest'
        }
    }
}
```

}

Save the file and commit it to GitHub

Step 4: Create Jenkins Pipeline (Browser)

Open:

http://localhost:8080

Click on "New Item"

Enter a name for your pipeline

Select "Pipeline"

Click OK

Step 5: Connect GitHub Repository

Scroll to the Pipeline section

Select "Pipeline script from SCM"

Choose SCM as Git

Enter Repository URL:

https://github.com/JeevanJeraldm/Devops-Lab.git

Set Branch to:

main

Click Save

Step 6: Add Docker Hub Credentials

Go to "Manage Jenkins"

Click "Credentials"

Add new credentials with:

Username: jeevanjeraldm
Password: Docker Hub password or access token
ID: dockerhub-creds

Save the credentials

Step 7: Run Pipeline

Open your Jenkins pipeline job

Click "Build Now"

Wait for the pipeline to execute

Step 8: Verify Output

Open browser and go to:

http://localhost:5000

Execution Summary

Jenkins pulls code from GitHub

Builds Docker image

